The paper discusses properties of Primitive Pythagorean Triples (PPT) that have relevance in cryptography, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of PPT in generating events of different probability, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the indexing of PPT, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of PPT in applications such as random number generation, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
